WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.242
MAN:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.420 --> 00:04.580
CLARK:
You saved me.

00:04.755 --> 00:06.040
But that was the last time.

00:06.215 --> 00:09.582
JOHN: The burning sun may strengthen you,
but it has the opposite effect on me.

00:09.760 --> 00:11.341
It stripped me of my powers.

00:12.262 --> 00:14.048
Detective John Jones.

00:14.223 --> 00:17.056
I wanted to be close by
in case you needed me.

00:17.893 --> 00:19.474
[G ROANS]

00:21.021 --> 00:22.056
OUVER:
Lana?

00:22.231 --> 00:24.187
Does Clark know about you?

00:24.358 --> 00:27.020
I can safely say he knows
more of my secrets than yours.

00:27.194 --> 00:30.106
You weren't planning on coming back,
were you?

00:31.031 --> 00:34.774
TESS: Mr. Luthor is a ﬁrm believer
in truth and justice.

00:34.952 --> 00:36.658
He's done more for this world
than you will.

00:36.829 --> 00:40.196
He dedicated his life to making it
a safer place.

00:42.251 --> 00:43.957
Dispatch, this is Detective Jones.

00:44.128 --> 00:45.743
Tell me you have a 20
on my suspect.

00:45.921 --> 00:48.333
MAN [OVER RADIO]: Suspect reported
turning north on Riverside.

00:48.507 --> 00:50.623
Black and white in pursuit.

00:50.801 --> 00:52.166
[TIRES SQUEAL]

00:52.344 --> 00:53.880
[POLICE SIREN WAILING]

00:58.976 --> 00:59.965
[TIRES SQUEAL]

01:29.590 --> 01:31.581
You're under arrest
for three counts of murder.

01:37.181 --> 01:38.967
Thanks for your assistance, ofﬁcers.

01:40.017 --> 01:42.178
Just doing ourjob, detective.

01:56.325 --> 01:57.815
[THUD]

02:12.341 --> 02:13.376
[GUN COCKS]

02:22.559 --> 02:23.810
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

02:28.899 --> 02:34.019
This isn't exactly what I had in mind
when I suggested coffee after work.

02:35.405 --> 02:37.066
After work?

02:38.033 --> 02:39.068
Lana, what time is it?

02:39.243 --> 02:43.282
Relax. It gives me a chance to see
Clark Kent in his new element.

02:44.289 --> 02:45.324
Shirt and tie.

02:45.499 --> 02:47.740
You must be turning heads left and right.

02:50.504 --> 02:53.246
I guess I've been too busy at work
to notice.

02:53.423 --> 02:55.038
With everything else going on.

02:57.135 --> 02:59.547
Any leads on that thing that took Chloe?

03:01.890 --> 03:03.926
A night watchman
and two ambulance drivers...

03:04.101 --> 03:06.387
...were murdered
the night of the ceremony.

03:06.562 --> 03:09.099
Lana, I'm gonna ﬁnd this thing
before it hurts anyone else.

03:09.273 --> 03:11.013
I know you will.

03:11.984 --> 03:15.226
You've become the man
that I've always known you could be.

03:19.449 --> 03:22.782
I should probably leave you to it.

03:22.953 --> 03:24.864
Next round's on you?

03:25.455 --> 03:29.243
WOMAN [OVER SPEAKER]: Emergency staff
to the ER. Incoming trauma, Metropolis P. D.

03:29.418 --> 03:32.205
MAN:
All right, let's go. Got a GSW.

03:32.379 --> 03:33.960
WOMAN:
GSW to the chest.

03:34.131 --> 03:35.996
BP is critical.
He's lost a lot of blood.

03:36.174 --> 03:37.914
He's alive, but we can't get a pulse.

03:38.093 --> 03:41.551
EMIL: I'll take it from here.
No one in or out without my authorization.

03:42.598 --> 03:44.179
WOMAN:
Clearing the wound. BP's dropping.

03:44.349 --> 03:45.805
EMIL:
We've gotta get the bullet out.

03:45.976 --> 03:47.807
Charge the paddles.
We're losing him. Clear.

04:44.743 --> 04:46.028
OLIVER:
Clark?

04:46.203 --> 04:48.660
Oliver? What are you doing here?

04:48.830 --> 04:51.367
l was out on patrol.
I heard the call go out over my scanner.

04:51.541 --> 04:53.668
Whoever that is,
he can't just operate on Jones.

04:53.835 --> 04:55.166
Why, because he's Martian?

04:56.296 --> 05:00.084
| get it. Clark, it's ﬁne.
He's in good hands with Emil, trust me.

05:00.258 --> 05:02.419
After I got poisoned,
I ﬁgured guys like us...

05:02.594 --> 05:05.210
...could probably use a specialist
on the payroll.

05:05.555 --> 05:07.341
Since when did Jones become one of us?

05:07.516 --> 05:10.349
He's gotten me out of a few
tight scrapes with the police.

05:12.771 --> 05:16.309
He wanted to meet with me
after his shift to talk about something.

05:16.483 --> 05:20.226
If he hadn't sacriﬁced his abilities
that bullet wouldn't have left a scratch.

05:20.404 --> 05:23.487
Now you feel guilty, that's your thing,
and I get it. That's great.

05:23.657 --> 05:26.569
But standing here doing nothing
is not gonna solve anything.

05:29.663 --> 05:33.326
-Do you know what he was working on?
-No.

05:34.251 --> 05:37.163
I think you should follow your leads.
And I'll follow mine.

05:37.337 --> 05:40.500
Hey, let's face it, teamwork's
never really been our strong suit.

05:42.718 --> 05:44.083
[SIGHS]

05:56.106 --> 05:57.141
What is your focus?

05:57.315 --> 05:59.271
True victory.

06:02.446 --> 06:04.107
And what is true victory?

06:04.281 --> 06:05.691
Victory over oneself.

06:05.866 --> 06:06.946
[TESS SIGHS]

06:08.118 --> 06:09.733
First principle of aikido.

06:11.788 --> 06:13.824
That will be all, Terrence.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.746
The enigmatic Lana Lang...

06:22.924 --> 06:24.915
...in the ﬂesh.

06:25.093 --> 06:26.708
To what do I owe this honor?

06:26.887 --> 06:29.128
I wanted to thank you.

06:29.306 --> 06:32.890
There's been a startling lack of coverage
on my return in the Daily Planet.

06:33.060 --> 06:35.722
I tend to keep my reporters
on a short leash.

06:35.896 --> 06:36.931
Hmm.

06:37.105 --> 06:38.140
Most of the time.

06:41.568 --> 06:46.562
You have just as much presence
as Lex said you did.

06:48.700 --> 06:51.817
You'd have to, to tame a Luthor.

06:53.038 --> 06:58.328
High marks, coming from the woman
entrusted with the Luthor legacy.

06:59.044 --> 07:01.160
He must have had a lot of faith in you.

07:03.173 --> 07:05.835
It wasn't easy to earn.

07:06.468 --> 07:08.709
I wonder how much of that trust
would remain...

07:08.887 --> 07:10.627
...if he knew how much
of his money...

07:10.806 --> 07:14.424
...you were siphoning
into a project called Prometheus.

07:14.976 --> 07:16.182
Unless, of course...

07:16.353 --> 07:19.516
...there's still someone higher than you
calling the shots.

07:23.819 --> 07:25.684
Lex is alive.

07:26.530 --> 07:28.896
And you know where he is, don't you?

07:29.658 --> 07:30.738
[SNICKERS]

07:33.453 --> 07:37.867
It seems that you've been wasting
a very gifted imagination, Miss Lang.

07:39.126 --> 07:42.209
The Planet runs a ﬁction section
on Sundays, if you're interested.

07:42.379 --> 07:45.246
| used to see that look in the mirror.

07:45.924 --> 07:49.508
You'll do anything to defend Lex,
to protect him.

07:52.055 --> 07:55.798
He has a way of turning
that kind of devotion against you.

07:56.518 --> 07:59.055
Well, you don't know Lex like I do.

08:00.605 --> 08:03.096
For your sake, I hope you're right.

08:13.743 --> 08:15.244
[MACHINE BEEPING]

08:21.126 --> 08:23.242
[CLARK SWOOSHES]

08:24.921 --> 08:26.502
Glad I caught you before you left.

08:26.673 --> 08:29.460
| just need to be back at the hospital
before Jimmy wakes up.

08:29.634 --> 08:32.296
-I wouldn't have asked but--
-Heroes don't take holidays.

08:32.470 --> 08:34.677
So from what I can hack,
our favorite Martian...

08:34.848 --> 08:39.387
...has been pulling proﬁles from a handful
of ofﬁcers from the 44th precinct.

08:42.272 --> 08:46.766
You know, I gotta say, being at the mercy
of modern technology really sucks.

08:46.943 --> 08:49.480
I know, I know.
I'm happy to be Brainiac-free.

08:49.654 --> 08:53.772
But my evil upgrade
was really convenient.

08:53.950 --> 08:56.282
Just glad everything's back to normal.

08:57.120 --> 08:58.701
So it would seem.

09:01.458 --> 09:04.120
How are things
now that Lana's back in your orbit?

09:04.294 --> 09:06.285
It's not like that.

09:08.089 --> 09:09.124
I think.

09:10.592 --> 09:11.798
Things always get messy...

09:11.968 --> 09:14.630
...when you start throwing around
the Clark-Lana triangle.

09:14.804 --> 09:18.968
I'm speaking from experience when I say
that the third point always hurts.

09:20.894 --> 09:22.725
I'm not trying to hurt anyone.

09:24.189 --> 09:25.395
How about Lois?

09:27.776 --> 09:29.641
Yeah, it's that obvious.

09:30.445 --> 09:32.527
Whoa, Lois.

09:32.989 --> 09:35.401
Lois is so....

09:35.575 --> 09:36.815
Lois?

09:37.160 --> 09:38.195
Yeah.

09:38.370 --> 09:39.530
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

09:42.707 --> 09:45.244
But seeing Lana come back,
it's like she never left.

09:49.130 --> 09:52.258
You can't just stop loving someone,
you know, just like that, right?

09:55.303 --> 09:56.884
I understand the need for closure.

09:57.055 --> 10:01.344
Just promise you're not gonna slam
my cousin in the door.

10:06.106 --> 10:09.018
Ballistics says
it's a 36-49 armor-piercing bullet.

10:10.527 --> 10:12.939
Which mysteriously vanished
from the evidence.

10:13.113 --> 10:15.399
Clark, you said you returned that,
didn't you?

10:15.573 --> 10:16.983
I did, Chloe.

10:19.202 --> 10:21.693
You said Jones was looking into
the 44th.

10:21.871 --> 10:25.363
Only someone from that system
could have stolen the evidence.

10:25.917 --> 10:27.657
This could have been an inside job.

10:27.836 --> 10:29.997
You think Jones was shot by a cop.

10:30.171 --> 10:33.208
If that's the case, someone higher up
in the force needs to know about this.

10:33.383 --> 10:34.418
[CH UCKLES]

10:34.592 --> 10:38.176
And you think someone on the force
is just gonna open up to you, a reporter?

10:38.346 --> 10:40.007
Clark, these guys protect their own.

10:40.181 --> 10:42.172
Jones is ﬁghting for his life.

10:42.350 --> 10:44.887
I'm not gonna let who did this
hide behind their badge.

10:47.022 --> 10:50.480
All right. If we're gonna sneak you
across this thin blue line...

10:50.650 --> 10:53.983
...you're gonna need something
more substantial than just a press pass.

11:06.499 --> 11:08.114
Danny boy.

11:08.293 --> 11:10.033
You all set for your new sidekick?

11:10.211 --> 11:11.587
He was born ready.

11:11.755 --> 11:14.121
Besides, who could resist
this handsome face?

11:14.299 --> 11:17.507
Better than looking
at his ugly mug all day.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.417
Give him hell, Danny.

11:19.596 --> 11:21.302
Come on, let's go.

11:25.268 --> 11:27.680
You the transfer from Coast City?

11:28.104 --> 11:30.811
Joe, ready to save the world?

11:32.901 --> 11:34.061
[SIGHS]

11:52.712 --> 11:54.668
That's quite a sweet tooth you got there.

11:54.839 --> 11:55.874
Yeah.

11:56.049 --> 11:59.132
Got them for my kid last Halloween,
now I can't stop eating the things.

11:59.302 --> 12:02.009
He loves banana.
Root beer's the only one worth the effort.

12:02.180 --> 12:03.295
Help yourself.

12:05.892 --> 12:08.804
What's the matter?
Don't they have squad cars in Coast City?

12:10.480 --> 12:13.313
I guess I'm not used to riding
in one so nice.

12:13.483 --> 12:14.472
Nice?

12:14.651 --> 12:18.064
Good to see you got a sense of humor.
You're gonna need that here.

12:19.823 --> 12:22.656
Let's hope you live long enough
to catch that surf again.

12:24.327 --> 12:27.319
There was a detective that got shot, right?
What's his name?

12:27.497 --> 12:28.532
Jones?

12:28.706 --> 12:31.834
Yeah, well, that might be a headline
back where you come from.

12:32.001 --> 12:36.415
But here, some detective getting plugged
is just another day in Metropolis.

12:42.554 --> 12:45.011
Blood on a badge
is blood on a badge, right?

12:45.181 --> 12:46.967
No matter what city you're in.

12:47.142 --> 12:50.976
Wearing this badge is like putting
a bull's-eye right over your heart.

12:51.146 --> 12:54.809
Meanwhile, we got these costumed idiots
running around...

12:54.983 --> 12:57.850
...getting in our way,
taking all the credit.

12:58.027 --> 13:00.860
The Green Arrow, the Red-Blue Blur.

13:01.990 --> 13:03.776
The Great Pumpkin.

13:03.950 --> 13:04.985
[CH UCKLES]

13:05.160 --> 13:06.650
Yeah.

13:07.537 --> 13:09.277
You think they do more harm than good?

13:09.456 --> 13:13.165
What I know is that cops got rules,
capes don't.

13:13.877 --> 13:16.334
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]: Metro Adam 13,
10-30 in progress...

13:16.504 --> 13:19.541
...550 South Broad, respond,
code three.

13:19.716 --> 13:21.832
10-4, Dispatch.

13:22.010 --> 13:24.547
Junkie's hitting the pharmacy again.

13:34.397 --> 13:36.262
Just someone I'm looking for.

13:37.609 --> 13:40.066
All right, you ready to see
how we do it in the big city?

13:40.236 --> 13:41.612
[POLICE SIREN WAILS]

13:52.207 --> 13:54.289
Make sure everyone's okay.

13:54.751 --> 13:56.582
DANNY:
Metro P.D. Stop!

13:59.088 --> 14:00.794
WOMAN:
Hey!

14:00.965 --> 14:02.000
DANNY:
Stop right there.

14:03.426 --> 14:04.461
Hold it!

14:22.904 --> 14:24.064
[GUNSHOT]

14:32.747 --> 14:35.329
You run track, Fordman?

14:35.500 --> 14:37.411
A little here and there.

14:39.546 --> 14:41.457
Guess I owe you one.

14:42.131 --> 14:43.792
DANNY:
You have the right to remain silent.

14:43.967 --> 14:47.050
Anything you say
can and will be used against you....

14:56.020 --> 14:57.430
[BEEPS]

14:59.649 --> 15:02.061
LANA: I'm uploading the ﬁles we
Wi-Fied from Tess' drives.

15:05.989 --> 15:08.696
Transmitting data to you now.

15:10.994 --> 15:11.983
Unknown?

15:23.339 --> 15:25.045
BOY: Hello.
-Whoa.

15:25.216 --> 15:26.251
CLARK:
Hey.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.882
Who are you, Warrior Angel?

15:28.052 --> 15:31.010
No. I'm the Red-Blue Blur.

15:33.683 --> 15:34.843
It's a losing battle.

15:35.018 --> 15:37.350
Don't worry, Dad. He'll grow out of it.

15:37.520 --> 15:40.136
You must be Joe.
I'm Danny's wife, Suzie.

15:40.315 --> 15:43.398
Hi. It's nice to meet you in person.

15:44.569 --> 15:46.184
In person?

15:46.362 --> 15:48.944
You are not still carrying
that picture around?

15:49.115 --> 15:51.572
He's had that thing since senior year.

15:56.539 --> 15:57.528
BOY:
Dad.

16:02.253 --> 16:03.288
You all right?

16:03.463 --> 16:04.919
DANNY:
You want the ambulance?

16:05.089 --> 16:07.250
Thanks for looking out for him today.

16:08.301 --> 16:10.462
Losing his partner really tore him up.

16:12.263 --> 16:15.130
It's good to know that
someone's still got his back out there.

16:17.101 --> 16:20.343
-How long did they ride together?
-Since they graduated the academy.

16:20.521 --> 16:23.649
One day they both went out,
and only Danny came home.

16:25.485 --> 16:28.898
Mike always thought he was bulletproof.

16:30.490 --> 16:34.108
Now every night I hold my breath
waiting for him to walk through that door.

16:40.667 --> 16:42.658
We just need him more.

16:45.672 --> 16:47.253
SIMMONS:
Hey, Fordman.

16:47.799 --> 16:49.505
Rookie really earned his keep today.

16:52.095 --> 16:53.756
And us.

16:54.681 --> 16:56.592
We all made it home safe.

16:57.183 --> 16:59.890
May we all be as lucky tomorrow.

17:03.981 --> 17:06.063
Excuse me.

17:08.486 --> 17:11.023
It's too bad all of us weren't so lucky.

17:15.284 --> 17:16.660
Yeah.

17:17.161 --> 17:18.446
Yeah, you know.

17:18.621 --> 17:21.237
The damn shame is,
nobody knew the guy.

17:21.708 --> 17:23.323
Ask anyone in his precinct.

17:24.544 --> 17:28.036
Lone wolf like Jones, you know,
he stands out from the pack...

17:28.214 --> 17:29.920
...and that's not a good thing.

17:30.091 --> 17:31.547
Safety in numbers?

17:32.176 --> 17:34.963
Well, I wasn't making light
when I said we're all brothers.

17:35.138 --> 17:37.629
Hard to stick your neck out
for a guy you don't know.

17:38.141 --> 17:41.178
Isn't that what police ofﬁcers
are supposed to do?

17:44.021 --> 17:45.056
[LAUGHS]

17:48.025 --> 17:50.641
Can you believe the stones on this guy?

17:51.529 --> 17:53.861
Good for you, Joe. Good for you.

17:55.575 --> 17:58.362
Listen, you keep your eyes on the street.

17:58.536 --> 18:01.699
And you leave the detective work
to the desk jockeys.

18:01.873 --> 18:03.989
And don't be stupid like Jones.

18:04.167 --> 18:06.874
Always wear your vest.

18:11.466 --> 18:13.127
[PAGER BEEPS]

18:16.888 --> 18:20.096
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

18:26.314 --> 18:28.179
Fordman, we gotta go.

18:46.334 --> 18:49.952
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

18:51.589 --> 18:54.581
I guess I'm not as good
a judge of character as I thought.

18:55.468 --> 19:00.258
It seems that you stole
some sensitive information from me.

19:01.265 --> 19:02.846
And I thought we were bonding.

19:03.017 --> 19:04.723
Rain check on girls' night?

19:06.354 --> 19:09.892
You know, it's nice to ﬁnally see
what Lex saw in you.

19:12.235 --> 19:14.226
You're stunning...

19:14.403 --> 19:15.779
...and devious.

19:16.906 --> 19:19.067
What Lex saw in me...

19:19.242 --> 19:21.233
...was an equal.

19:21.410 --> 19:23.571
Someone that he couldn't control.

19:23.746 --> 19:25.327
Really?

19:26.749 --> 19:31.368
I guess I shouldn't send my condolences
about the miscarriage then.

19:33.548 --> 19:37.416
It gave me the perspective I needed
to see Lex for who he really is.

19:37.593 --> 19:38.708
[GUN COCKS]

19:40.346 --> 19:42.803
I know he thought
that was the only way to keep you...

19:43.683 --> 19:45.924
...but he always loved you.

19:46.936 --> 19:50.599
When you stole the data, you corrupted
our ﬁles and we've lost everything.

19:50.773 --> 19:53.515
Prometheus is the one chance
Lex has at survival...

19:53.693 --> 19:55.524
...and I won't let you jeopardize that.

20:52.668 --> 20:54.169
Got you a little present, Danny.

20:56.631 --> 20:57.666
Looks who's surfaced.

20:57.840 --> 20:59.455
Listen. I got acquitted, all right?

20:59.634 --> 21:02.376
The judge let me off,
no strings attached, all right?

21:02.553 --> 21:06.011
You got off on a technicality,
you piece of trash cop killer.

21:07.141 --> 21:09.974
Do you have any idea
what you did to my partner's family?

21:10.144 --> 21:11.350
And what you did to me?

21:11.520 --> 21:12.555
Danny.

21:12.730 --> 21:15.267
We may not control the system,
but we control the streets.

