Don't hold back.

21:26.786 --> 21:28.367
Justice must be served.

21:28.537 --> 21:30.243
MOB:
I'm sorry.

21:32.667 --> 21:34.658
TALBERT:
You just gonna stand there, Fordman?

21:34.835 --> 21:37.872
Or you gonna man up
and give your partner a hand?

21:41.884 --> 21:44.000
[WEAPON WHIRRING]

21:59.485 --> 22:02.352
-What the hell are you doing here?
-You gotta get out of here. Now.

22:12.915 --> 22:16.658
Were you this devoted
before or after your accident?

22:17.128 --> 22:19.744
Someone's been doing her homework.

22:22.008 --> 22:23.248
I don't know what you want.

22:23.426 --> 22:26.589
Two years ago, your survey team
was in South America...

22:26.762 --> 22:28.923
...collecting disease samples
for LuthorCorp...

22:29.098 --> 22:31.714
...when an explosion
destroyed your camp.

22:32.184 --> 22:33.685
And you were left for dead.

22:33.853 --> 22:36.185
Lex saved my life.

22:36.689 --> 22:38.270
I owe him everything.

22:38.441 --> 22:42.104
This is how a Luthor rewards
that kind of loyalty.

22:44.447 --> 22:45.436
What are you doing?

22:45.614 --> 22:47.570
I'm opening your eyes.

22:55.666 --> 22:59.079
There's a nano—transmitter
hardwired to your optic nerve.

22:59.253 --> 23:03.087
You've been Lex's eyes and ears
for quite some time.

23:03.841 --> 23:05.797
He's watching us right now.

23:17.021 --> 23:19.683
Lex might have saved you...

23:19.857 --> 23:21.893
...but he never trusted you, Tess.

23:29.658 --> 23:31.398
I'm
sorry

23:44.340 --> 23:47.002
I'll let you know as soon
as Detective Jones wakes up.

23:47.176 --> 23:49.007
He's strong,
but he's not out of the woods.

23:49.178 --> 23:50.839
Thank you, doctor.

23:51.472 --> 23:52.757
Fordman.

23:52.932 --> 23:54.923
-Look, take it easy.
-Take it easy?

23:55.101 --> 23:56.181
Come here.

23:56.352 --> 23:58.388
I saw you chatting up your buddy
the Green Arrow.

23:58.562 --> 24:00.848
He took down our squad
and you let him walk.

24:01.023 --> 24:04.231
-I don't know what you think you saw—
-All you do is ask about some detective...

24:04.401 --> 24:07.359
...and then I ﬁnd you checking up on him
in the hospital too?

24:07.530 --> 24:10.112
Who are you, Joe? You fed, IAB?

24:11.117 --> 24:14.780
I wanna take down the guy who shot him.
I know the shooter's a part of your squad.

24:15.913 --> 24:17.278
They crossed the line, Danny.

24:17.456 --> 24:20.539
This isn't ﬁrst they've gone after
who slipped through the system.

24:20.709 --> 24:23.371
-Well, someone has to.
-What about John Jones?

24:23.546 --> 24:25.457
He was onto your lynch mob,
wasn't he?

24:26.966 --> 24:30.299
Danny, someone shot him to cover it up.
Who are you protecting?

24:32.304 --> 24:34.795
You don't roll over on a badge, not ever.

24:34.974 --> 24:36.464
Why is it okay to shoot one?

24:38.644 --> 24:42.262
Hey, these guys have my back,
which is more than I can say for you.

24:42.439 --> 24:46.023
I do have your back, Danny,
and I might be the only one.

24:46.193 --> 24:47.808
This is notjustice.

24:52.116 --> 24:54.607
Joe, I'm just one man.

24:54.785 --> 24:57.322
I mean, what can one man do?

24:59.915 --> 25:03.373
Ask yourself why you put that uniform on
in the ﬁrst place.

25:20.769 --> 25:23.556
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

25:23.731 --> 25:28.771
Imagine my surprise when I stumbled
upon Metropolis' ﬁnest going gangland.

25:29.653 --> 25:31.939
Thug's a good look
for you and your crew.

25:32.114 --> 25:33.399
They're not all bad, Oliver.

25:33.574 --> 25:36.361
Some of them are out there every day
risking their lives...

25:36.535 --> 25:39.743
-...trying to do the same thing we are.
-Yeah, I'm sure you're right.

25:40.289 --> 25:43.406
| always forget, how many parolees
did we rough up last month?

25:43.584 --> 25:44.744
Do you remember?

25:44.919 --> 25:47.786
I thought you would understand
that this isn't black and white.

25:48.672 --> 25:51.914
No matter how noble their intentions,
these people have gone too far.

25:52.092 --> 25:53.298
And you never have?

25:55.679 --> 25:58.591
Danny watched that guy kill his partner.

25:58.766 --> 26:01.303
Tell me you've never been tempted
to look in the eyes of someone...

26:01.477 --> 26:03.217
...who committed so much pain and--

26:03.395 --> 26:04.475
Kill them?

26:06.106 --> 26:09.439
Kill them for the greater good? You're gonna
tell me that's what you believe?

26:11.820 --> 26:13.105
I didn't think so.

26:14.573 --> 26:17.315
What I'm saying is that saving someone,
truly saving them...

26:17.493 --> 26:20.405
...is not about knocking them out
and throwing them in a dark room.

26:20.579 --> 26:22.991
It's about helping them ﬁnd
their way back to the right side.

26:25.459 --> 26:28.417
You know what, Clark?
Some people are beyond saving.

26:30.464 --> 26:32.420
That's the suspect
that Jones tracked down.

26:32.591 --> 26:34.456
He didn't ﬁnd his way back to custody.

26:34.635 --> 26:37.342
He did manage to ﬁnd his way
to the bottom of a river.

26:37.513 --> 26:39.754
These cops are taking the law
in their own hands.

26:39.932 --> 26:42.173
How many have to die
before you do anything?

26:42.351 --> 26:44.683
Look, I've narrowed it down
to Simmons and Talbert.

26:44.853 --> 26:46.844
-Both have sniper training.
-Great.

26:47.022 --> 26:49.138
You sit here and you play detective.

26:49.316 --> 26:53.355
I'm gonna go make sure your boys
don't put another person in the hospital.

26:56.865 --> 26:59.527
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

27:17.344 --> 27:18.379
What's the matter?

27:19.263 --> 27:20.378
[SIGHS]

27:22.308 --> 27:24.890
There's something
you need to know about Joe.

27:25.060 --> 27:27.016
I made a couple of calls.

27:27.187 --> 27:29.849
He's not who he says he is.

28:01.638 --> 28:02.673
[POLICE SIREN WAILS]

28:02.848 --> 28:03.883
[TIRES SQUEAL]

28:04.058 --> 28:06.515
SIMMONS: Should've called.
I would've had the wife set a place.

28:06.685 --> 28:10.519
You're under arrest for the attempted
murder of Detective John Jones.

28:14.693 --> 28:15.899
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

28:17.029 --> 28:18.064
You set me up?

28:21.950 --> 28:23.281
You're better than this.

28:40.135 --> 28:42.171
You did the right thing.

28:42.346 --> 28:44.758
There's one loose thread to tie up.

28:46.475 --> 28:49.592
And your hands have been clean
for way too long, Danny boy.

28:50.479 --> 28:52.310
Hey, smile.

28:52.481 --> 28:55.769
You're gonna be the man who killed
the Green Arrow.

29:18.298 --> 29:20.835
This is messed up.
You said you were transferring me.

29:21.009 --> 29:23.466
I'm not gonna kill you.
You're just the bait.

29:23.637 --> 29:25.969
SIMMONS [OVER EARWIG]:
You ready, Danny?

29:27.516 --> 29:28.631
[G ROANS]

29:28.809 --> 29:31.175
How do you know
the Arrow's gonna show?

29:31.353 --> 29:33.469
SIMMONS [OVER EARWIG]:
He can 't help himself.

29:34.314 --> 29:37.772
After the other night,
you can bet he's been watching us.

29:38.193 --> 29:40.354
Help! Help!

29:40.529 --> 29:42.110
Help!

29:43.949 --> 29:45.655
Somebody help me!

29:50.372 --> 29:53.205
That should do it. Let him have it.

29:54.001 --> 29:55.081
[GRUNTS]

29:55.794 --> 29:58.331
MAN [OVER RADIO]: Target spotted
moving toward your position.

29:58.505 --> 29:59.790
Showtime, kid.

30:06.513 --> 30:07.969
We gotta stop meeting like this.

30:14.813 --> 30:16.053
You're welcome.

30:16.231 --> 30:17.732
Damn it, Turpin, move in.

30:18.317 --> 30:21.229
DANNY:
Turn around. Show me your hands.

30:25.699 --> 30:27.564
That's not bad.

30:27.743 --> 30:29.904
It's not every day
someone gets the drop on me.

30:30.078 --> 30:32.569
Is this all a joke to you?
That guy took a shot at me.

30:32.748 --> 30:35.740
And you were gonna what,
put him in the ground?

30:35.918 --> 30:38.534
SIMMONS [OVER EARWIG]: Damn it, Turpin,
you got the shot. Take it.

30:42.716 --> 30:43.751
Joe's partner, right?

30:45.928 --> 30:47.259
His name is Clark Kent.

30:48.096 --> 30:49.927
This isn't about him, okay?

30:50.098 --> 30:52.259
You got the shot, Danny.
Come on, take it.

30:52.434 --> 30:54.891
It's not too late for you.
You don't have to do this.

30:55.062 --> 30:58.054
Why don't you capes
just mind your own damn business, huh?

30:58.232 --> 31:00.314
You don't know these guys like I do.

31:00.484 --> 31:02.099
I got a family at home.

31:02.694 --> 31:04.400
When your boy asks who you saved...

31:04.571 --> 31:06.778
...you tell him
you killed a man in cold blood.

31:07.157 --> 31:08.442
It ain't like that.

31:08.617 --> 31:11.575
I knew you were part of this,
but Clark actually trusted you.

31:11.745 --> 31:13.451
He thinks you just lost your way.

31:13.622 --> 31:15.283
SIMMONS:
Take the shot, Danny.

31:19.294 --> 31:24.084
Man, if this is what you need to do
to ﬁnd yourself, then....

31:27.678 --> 31:28.713
Then do it.

31:29.721 --> 31:31.632
You do it, you pull the trigger...

31:31.807 --> 31:33.968
...and you can prove Clark wrong.

31:36.353 --> 31:38.435
Be a real hero.

31:38.605 --> 31:40.596
Take the shot, Danny.

31:59.626 --> 32:00.832
[GUNSHOT]

32:05.757 --> 32:08.248
You should've pulled that trigger, kid.

32:08.927 --> 32:10.337
Dispatch.

32:10.512 --> 32:13.254
Green Arrow spotted on 16th Avenue
assaulting an ofﬁcer.

32:13.432 --> 32:15.923
Requesting backup. Ofﬁcer is down.

32:18.353 --> 32:21.470
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]: All units, all units,
10-108 on 16th.

32:21.648 --> 32:24.765
Officer under attack from Green Arrow.
Immediate backup requested.

32:24.943 --> 32:28.185
How many times did I swear
Turpin wouldn't seal the deal?

32:28.905 --> 32:29.940
POLICEMAN:
Pay up.

32:30.616 --> 32:31.651
[CLARK SWOOSHES]

32:36.455 --> 32:37.490
[GUNSHOT]

32:42.544 --> 32:43.533
[GUNSHOT]

32:45.213 --> 32:46.669
Come on.

32:52.054 --> 32:53.089
[CLARK SWOOSHES]

33:04.316 --> 33:05.351
How did...?

33:05.525 --> 33:06.810
CLARK:
It's like you said...

33:07.986 --> 33:10.398
...always wear a vest.

33:10.739 --> 33:12.400
[SIMON GRUNTING]

33:14.242 --> 33:15.493
[POLICE SIREN WAILS]

33:23.502 --> 33:26.539
-Danny.
-You're under arrest.

33:27.297 --> 33:28.912
Don't shoot.

33:29.966 --> 33:32.093
I'm one of the good guys.

33:49.861 --> 33:52.523
-Hey.
OLIVER: Hey.

33:53.365 --> 33:56.277
Uh, feels good
to be back on my feet again.

33:56.451 --> 33:57.486
[GRUNTS]

33:58.036 --> 34:00.903
I don't know how many favors
you had to call in.

34:01.373 --> 34:03.614
Thank you for getting me out of trouble
with the police.

34:04.376 --> 34:05.786
It was the least I could do.

34:06.294 --> 34:08.785
You could have used some backup
out there.

34:08.964 --> 34:10.500
Why didn't you call me in sooner?

34:11.133 --> 34:14.000
The same reason I've had to pull you
from the brink of death.

34:16.805 --> 34:19.137
The same reason
you let your guard down last night.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.685
Pride.

34:25.105 --> 34:30.475
After knowing what it's like
to truly feel powerful...

34:31.319 --> 34:34.482
...to have the ability to change fate...

34:35.782 --> 34:38.273
...it's hard to admit
when you can't do it alone.

34:40.328 --> 34:42.660
Going solo's
really caught up with us lately, huh?

34:45.667 --> 34:49.159
You know, for everything
Danny's crew did wrong, I have to say...

34:50.088 --> 34:52.830
...knowing there's always someone there
who has your back...

34:54.176 --> 34:56.963
...that brotherhood can make you
feel you could do anything.

35:06.772 --> 35:11.232
When I thought my life was over,
you gave me a reason to keep going.

35:14.070 --> 35:16.857
I wouldn't be who I am without you.

35:20.327 --> 35:22.238
I trusted you.

35:24.456 --> 35:26.697
Because I respected you.

35:29.836 --> 35:33.579
I've done everything you've ever asked.

35:34.257 --> 35:36.168
You've seen that...

35:36.885 --> 35:41.879
...with your own eyes,
and apparently with mine.

35:44.684 --> 35:46.549
But not anymore.

35:49.981 --> 35:52.472
I hope you watch with rapt attention...

35:52.651 --> 35:54.312
...as your bank accounts close...

35:54.486 --> 35:56.693
...as you lose all contact
with the outside world...

35:56.863 --> 36:00.902
...as your life disappears...

36:01.076 --> 36:03.158
...before your eyes.

36:07.582 --> 36:08.992
[BEEPING]

36:15.257 --> 36:17.213
Goodbye, Lex.

36:25.559 --> 36:27.390
I loved you...

36:28.436 --> 36:30.973
...you son of a bitch.

36:38.363 --> 36:39.864
Mercy.

36:42.701 --> 36:43.781
Wow!

36:44.786 --> 36:46.993
I sure hope your s'mores
are worth the drive.

36:48.957 --> 36:51.744
We wouldn't want you to spoil
your appetite.

36:51.918 --> 36:53.783
We're going to dinner.

36:54.212 --> 36:56.203
I'd like to discuss a merger.

36:56.381 --> 36:57.837
[CHUCKLES]

36:58.592 --> 37:00.173
A merger?

37:01.636 --> 37:02.887
What kind of merger?

37:04.306 --> 37:06.137
Any kind you want.

37:07.475 --> 37:09.090
Don't keep me waiting.

37:22.490 --> 37:26.483
Oh. All right, bud, p.j. time, okay?

37:33.376 --> 37:34.411
Green Arrow?

37:35.503 --> 37:37.414
No. Robin Hood.

37:37.589 --> 37:40.831
You know, most people think
he's a bad guy, but he isn't.

37:41.009 --> 37:43.216
That's what my kid tells me. Go ﬁgure.

37:43.386 --> 37:44.967
Must be all those bright colors.

37:48.725 --> 37:51.182
Danny, I'm sorry I couldn't tell you
I was a reporter.

37:52.437 --> 37:55.520
Yeah, well,
I can't really be mad at you, Clark.

37:55.690 --> 37:59.603
I wanna be, but you were just doing
what you felt was right.

37:59.778 --> 38:03.441
Which is more than I can say for myself.

38:03.990 --> 38:07.653
I just got all turned around.

38:08.828 --> 38:10.409
I'm glad you found your way again.

38:10.997 --> 38:13.909
Yeah, well, let's hold off on that
until the inquest next week.

38:16.086 --> 38:17.542
But no matter what happens...

38:20.340 --> 38:22.547
...I know they can be proud of me
from now on.

38:28.682 --> 38:29.762
Hey, Danny.

38:31.977 --> 38:35.515
Is it hard to put them through
what you do every day?

38:37.565 --> 38:41.103
You just can't lose sight of the people
you're trying to protect, you know?

38:41.277 --> 38:43.404
It'd be harder not doing it.

38:45.907 --> 38:48.114
I do what I do...

38:49.411 --> 38:51.026
...just to keep them safe.

38:55.750 --> 38:56.739
Yeah, yeah.

38:58.086 --> 39:00.042
What about you, Clark?

39:00.755 --> 39:03.132
You got someone
who makes it all worth it?

39:15.979 --> 39:17.310
[ESPRESSO MACHINE HISSES]

39:28.450 --> 39:30.941
If I squintjust right,
it's like we're 14 again.

39:32.579 --> 39:34.991
You say that like it's a good thing.

39:35.623 --> 39:36.703
What's up?

39:38.543 --> 39:40.534
I couldn't sleep.

39:40.712 --> 39:43.374
So you came to a coffee shop?

39:45.258 --> 39:47.670
Not your best plan, Mr. Kent.

39:49.846 --> 39:52.758
Lana, I know you had reasons
for coming back.

39:54.267 --> 39:55.552
Why are you staying?

39:57.479 --> 40:00.095
Leaving's harder
than I thought it would be.

40:02.442 --> 40:06.856
But like I said,
I don't know how long I'll be here, so....

40:09.491 --> 40:13.325
Whether you leave in 10 years or tomorrow,
the important thing is you're here today.

40:16.414 --> 40:17.995
Clark.

40:20.251 --> 40:21.991
We aren't 14 anymore.

40:22.170 --> 40:24.877
The world will always be bigger
than the both of us.

40:25.048 --> 40:28.006
Maybe it doesn't have to be
all or nothing.

40:29.260 --> 40:30.511
[SIGHS]

40:32.263 --> 40:34.128
For the last year...

40:35.016 --> 40:38.508
...all I've done is sacriﬁce myself
and everything that I loved...

40:38.686 --> 40:40.642
...for the greater good.

40:41.773 --> 40:42.979
[CLARK SIGHS]

40:46.653 --> 40:48.939
What if the rest of the world
didn't have to come ﬁrst?

40:50.031 --> 40:51.817
The world needs you, Clark.

40:53.118 --> 40:55.154
What about what we need?

42:07.817 --> 42:09.808
[ENGLISH SDH]
